# ManageR2 Architecture Rules

## Monorepo Layout

```
ManageR2-System/
  apps/
    web/        # Vite + React + TypeScript SPA
    api/        # ASP.NET Core C# backend (solution root)
  database/SP/  # SQL stored procedures
```

---

# Backend — Clean Architecture

## Layer stack

```
ManageR2.Api  →  ManageR2.Infrastructure  →  ManageR2.Domain
(HTTP/DTOs)      (Repos / Services / Models)   (Entities / Enums)
```

Forbidden: Domain → Api or Domain → Infrastructure.

## Feature-based folders

Each domain has its own folder in every layer:

```
apps/api/
  ManageR2.Api/Features/<Domain>/
    <Domain>Controller.cs
    DTOs/
  ManageR2.Infrastructure/Features/<Domain>/
    Repositories/   Services/   Models/
  ManageR2.Domain/Features/<Domain>/
    Entities/   Exceptions/
```

Domains: Projects, WorkItems, Users, Employees, Customers, Sites, Contacts, Reports, SmartAssignment, AdvancedSmartAssignment.

## Layer responsibilities

**Api** — HTTP only: routing, model binding, DTOs, status codes. Controllers must be thin; call Services (or Repositories when no business logic). No SQL, no business logic.

**Infrastructure** — Services (business logic) and Repositories (DB access only). Services call Repositories. Repositories use ADO.NET + Stored Procedures exclusively. No EF, no inline SQL.

**Domain** — Entities, Enums, Exceptions, interfaces. No dependencies on Api or Infrastructure.

## SQL Rules

All SQL lives in SQL Server. Allowed objects: Stored Procedures, Functions, Views. Inline SQL in C# is forbidden. SQL scripts → `database/SP/sp_<Domain>_<Action>.sql`.

## Dependency Injection

Register in `ManageR2.Api/Program.cs`:
- `AddScoped<IXRepository, XRepository>()`
- `AddScoped<IXService, XService>()`

