# Frontend — React (apps/web/src/)

## Folder layout

```
apps/web/src/
  app/                     # router, providers, ProtectedRoute, AppLayout
  features/<domain>/       # one folder per business domain
    components/<Name>/     # component folder (Name.tsx + Name.css + index.ts)
    hooks/
    pages/<Page>/
    api/                   # <domain>ApiClient.ts
    types.ts
    index.ts
  shared/
    components/<Name>/     # common UI (Button, Modal, Spinner, Table, …)
    hooks/   utils/
  api/                     # client.ts, auth.ts
  styles/                  # tokens.css, base.css, utilities.css
```

Dependency flow: `app` → `features` → `shared` → `api`. No cross-feature deep imports.

## Component folder rule

Every non-trivial component is a folder:

```
ComponentName/
  ComponentName.tsx
  ComponentName.css   ← scoped BEM styles
  index.ts            ← re-export only
```

## Frontend conventions

- Thin components: pages call hooks and render; hooks fetch and map.
- All HTTP calls through `@api/client.ts → apiRequest<T>()`.
- JWT in `sessionStorage` keys `manager2_*`. `ProtectedRoute` wraps all protected routes.
- Reuse tokens from `src/styles/tokens.css` via CSS variables.
- RTL layout: `<html dir="rtl">` + Hebrew text; do not hard-code directional values.

---

# Git Workflow

Never commit directly to `dev`. Feature branches only:

```
feature/projects-react-page
feature/workitems-service-layer
```

One focused task per branch.

---

# Cursor Behavior

- Preserve architecture; avoid unnecessary rewrites.
- Prefer patch-based changes; do not touch unrelated code.
- Explain risky changes.
- Keep controllers thin, repositories DB-only, components presentational.
